sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Client
    participant TTC as TimeTrackingController
    participant TTS as TimeTrackingService
    participant TER as TimeEntryRepository
    participant TAR as TaskAssigneeRepository
    participant EE as EventEmitter
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    Note over C,DB: === START TIMER ===

    C->>TTC: POST /api/v1/tasks/:taskId/time/start
    TTC->>TTS: startTimer(taskId, currentUser)

    TTS->>TAR: isUserAssigned(taskId, userId)
    TAR->>DB: SELECT FROM task_assignees WHERE task_id=? AND user_id=?
    DB-->>TAR: Result

    alt Not assigned and not Manager+
        TTS-->>TTC: throw ForbiddenException
        TTC-->>C: 403 {error: "Must be assigned to task or have manager role"}
    end

    TTS->>TER: findActiveByUser(userId)
    TER->>DB: SELECT * FROM time_entries WHERE user_id=? AND end_time IS NULL
    DB-->>TER: Active entry or null

    alt Has active timer on ANOTHER task
        TTS-->>TTC: throw ConflictException
        TTC-->>C: 409 {error: "Active timer exists", data: {activeEntry}}
    end

    alt Has active timer on SAME task
        TTS-->>TTC: throw ConflictException
        TTC-->>C: 409 {error: "Timer already running on this task"}
    end

    TTS->>TTS: Create TimeEntry {task_id, user_id, start_time: NOW()}
    TTS->>TER: save(timeEntry)
    TER->>DB: INSERT INTO time_entries (task_id, user_id, start_time)
    DB-->>TER: Created entry
    TER-->>TTS: TimeEntry entity

    TTS->>EE: emit('time.started', {entry, user})
    TTS-->>TTC: TimeEntry
    TTC-->>C: 201 {data: timeEntry}

    Note over C,DB: === STOP TIMER ===

    C->>TTC: POST /api/v1/tasks/:taskId/time/stop
    TTC->>TTS: stopTimer(taskId, currentUser)

    TTS->>TER: findActiveByUserAndTask(userId, taskId)
    TER->>DB: SELECT * FROM time_entries WHERE user_id=? AND task_id=? AND end_time IS NULL
    DB-->>TER: Active entry or null

    alt No active timer on this task
        TTS-->>TTC: throw NotFoundException
        TTC-->>C: 404 {error: "No active timer on this task"}
    end

    TTS->>TTS: Set end_time = NOW()
    TTS->>TTS: Compute duration_seconds = EXTRACT(EPOCH FROM end_time - start_time)
    TTS->>TER: save(updatedEntry)
    TER->>DB: UPDATE time_entries SET end_time=?, duration_seconds=? WHERE id=?
    DB-->>TER: Updated entry
    TER-->>TTS: TimeEntry entity

    TTS->>EE: emit('time.stopped', {entry, duration})
    TTS-->>TTC: TimeEntry with duration
    TTC-->>C: 200 {data: timeEntry}

    Note over C,DB: === FORCE STOP & START (switch tasks) ===

    C->>TTC: POST /api/v1/tasks/:newTaskId/time/start?force=true
    TTC->>TTS: startTimer(newTaskId, currentUser, force=true)

    TTS->>TER: findActiveByUser(userId)
    TER-->>TTS: Active entry on oldTask

    alt force=true and active timer exists
        TTS->>TTS: Stop active timer (compute duration)
        TTS->>TER: save(stoppedEntry)
        TER->>DB: UPDATE time_entries SET end_time=NOW(), duration_seconds=...
        TTS->>EE: emit('time.stopped', {oldEntry})
    end

    TTS->>TTS: Create new TimeEntry for newTask
    TTS->>TER: save(newEntry)
    TER->>DB: INSERT INTO time_entries (...)
    TTS->>EE: emit('time.started', {newEntry})
    TTS-->>TTC: {stopped: oldEntry, started: newEntry}
    TTC-->>C: 201 {data: {stopped: oldEntry, started: newEntry}}
